Number of Sessions (per user)
The original pipeline (SessionPipeline.split_sessions) defines a custom split per user:

Training (genuine only): ~40 sessions (range 30–50 depending on user).

Test genuine: ~35–40 sessions.

Test impostor: ~20–25 sessions.

These numbers come from the hard‑coded slice indices in the split_sessions method. Example:

python
if(user_id == 'samanth'):
    train_genuine = genuine[50:90]
    test_genuine = genuine[90:]
    test_impostor = impostor
For most users the default is:

python
train_genuine = genuine[10:50]
test_genuine = genuine[50:]
test_impostor = impostor
Thus the exact counts vary by user. For the 10‑user LOUO tuning, the script simply loads whatever is in the CSV files; the split was already performed during CSV generation.

Important: The impostor sessions are recorded when a different person uses the same device as the genuine user. Therefore, an impostor session for user A cannot be used for user B (device context differs).

File Naming Conventions
Training files: <user_id>_training_sessions.csv

Testing files: <user_id>_testing_sessions.csv

The user ID is extracted by removing the suffix _training_sessions.csv from the filename.

CSV Column Names
Each CSV contains:

All features generated by SessionLevelFeatureExtractor (initially ~441 columns, expanded with per‑axis FFT, MFCC, Multitaper, etc. – total >500 now).

Metadata columns (used for labels and sometimes kept):

session_id

impostor_user_id (only in some versions)

label or session_label or test_type – the ground truth.

In the test CSVs, there is a dedicated label column (the scripts search for 'session_label', 'label', 'test_type'). The content is normalised to 'genuine' / 'impostor'. In the OCSVM training script, labels are converted to 1 (genuine) / -1 (impostor).

Typical feature names (examples):

nav_total_screens, nav_unique_screens

touch_duration_mean, touch_velocity_iqr

acc_magnitude_mean, acc_x_skew

gyro_magnitude_std, gyro_x_iqr

acc_fft_peak_freq, acc_fft_spectral_energy, …

acc_mag_mfcc_0_mean, acc_mag_mt_peak_freq, …

touch_HMOG_acc_x_stft_energy, etc.

A full list of original features (before Phase 1) can be found in the drop‑cols list of the training script (the ones explicitly commented out). The drop_cols array defines which columns are excluded.

